Package org.openbel.framework.common.model

The BEL common model.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BELModelObject BEL common model base class.
BELObject Represents components of the Biological Expression Language (BEL)
CommonConverter<T1 extends BELObject,T2> Interface for defining a converter between two reference types, where T1 is a BELObject.
 

Class Summary
Annotation An annotation applied to a BEL statement, referencing an annotation definition.
AnnotationDefinition Annotations express knowledge about a statement.
AnnotationGroup A grouping of annotations, evidence, and citation.
Citation A citation indicates some knowledge source is cited to support a statement.
CitationAuthorsAnnotationDefinition This is a specialization of annotation definitions specific to the identification of a citation.
CitationCommentAnnotationDefinition This is a specialization of annotation definitions specific to the description of a citation.
CitationDateAnnotationDefinition This is a specialization of annotation definitions specific to the date of a citation.
CitationNameAnnotationDefinition This is a specialization of annotation definitions specific to the name of a citation.
CitationReferenceAnnotationDefinition This is a specialization of annotation definitions specific to the identification of a citation.
CitationTypeAnnotationDefinition This is a specialization of annotation definitions specific to the type of a citation.
CommonModelFactory CommonModelFactory represents a factory for common model BEL objects.
DataFileIndex DataFileIndex represents an index BEL data file that allows efficient, lookup of key/value pairs stored on disk.
Document BEL documents are structured text documents which contain BEL statements along with sufficient additional information to fully describe and process the document.
EquivalenceDataIndex EquivalenceDataIndex represents a DataFileIndex that is bound to a source and target namespace.
Evidence Evidence in support of a statement.
EvidenceAnnotationDefinition TODO DOCUMENT
Header The header provides ownership and legal context for a BEL document.
Namespace Defines a namespace whose values may be used in statements.
NamespaceGroup Contains any number of namespaces.
Parameter BEL term function parameter.
Statement A statement is a specific assertion of a fact in some context: it is implicitly based on some source of knowledge, implicitly true in at least one specific situation.
Statement.Object Defines the object of a statement.
StatementGroup A group of BEL statements.
Term BEL terms represent biological entities.
